@NODE DOCZEGO

                                 Cashana

        I'm sure You're wondering what does this small program, with very
silly name :) The name is silly, but for Poles it's much silier then for
You, he he ;) (urgh!) This little tool lets You save Your favourite's WWW
Browser's (eg. IBrowse 1.12+, Voyager 2.83-) cache as HTML document with
(sub)directories and normal filenames. I made it, 'cause I had problem
with my IBrowse, which liked to kill my cache every time, I used it :(
Maybe You have no problems with it, but You may want to change your cache
to normal HTML doc - so it's for You.

        Cashana only reads, and processes filename's comment and uses it
to save proper files with proper names. It's very easy to use so let's
check it out! :)

@ENDNODE

@NODE DESCRIPTION "Details"

                              @{fg shine}Details@{fg text}

        @{b}Cashana@{ub} can be used only with CLI - like interfaces. It's
made especially for Opus 5+ and cooperates with it in 100%. It's of course
OK to use it with FileMaster or other filetool :^ If you like to write
looooooooong command lines - use CLI "by hand" ;))

        Program "eats" 2 arguments:

        CACHEFILE/A/M

        Name of cache file(s) from WWW Browser (cache usually is saved to
PROGDIR:Cache in most browsers). These files will be saved to

DESTDIR/A

in correct directories. Cashana will make all automaticly.

If you want to add this program to Opus' "User Menu" add this line in
configuration window:

AmigaDOS: Cashana {O} {d}

and switch these options on:

@{i}Change to source dir
Output to window (eventualy reader)@{ui}

        I think you know now how does it work? Just choose "Open local
file" from menu of your Browser and pick your HTML's index file. That's
all!

        If You don't like this program You may at any time change it,
using source (in E). But - please - all new versions of Cashana made by
You - should be sent to me (e-mail later). Also remember that Cashana is
Freeware!

@ENDNODE

@NODE REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

@{i}You need:@{ui}

- KS 2.0+,
- some RAM,
- HD.
- IBrowse, Voyager 2.88-

@{i}Program is tested with:@{ui}

A1200/030/10MB/HDD/3.0

also with Enforcer (no hits detected)

@ENDNODE
@NODE HISTORY "History"

@{b}History@{ub}

Version@{fg shine} 0.3@{fg text} (30.03.1998) 
- first public release.

Version@{fg shine} 0.35@{fg text} (04.05.1998) 
- now really works with old Voyager's cache :)
- tells You how many errors occured while working
- now reacts at CtrlC break signal.


@ENDNODE
